cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.CC

This paper focuses on assessing cognitive load on web search tasks, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and information retrieval (IR) aspects. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the study involves analyzing search system features and search tasks, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also examines individual differences among searchers, which could be related to natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL), making cs.CL another likely sub-category. The study involves controlled experiments, which could be related to cybernetics (cs.CY) and computing methodologies (cs.CC).
